Takes note with appreciation of the work of the Special Rapporteur on the rights to freedom of peaceful assembly and of association, and also takes note of the reports submitted to the Human Rights Council
A/HRC/50/23 and A/HRC/50/42, A/HRC/53/38, A/HRC/55/60, A/HRC/56/60 and A/HRC/59/44. and the General Assembly,
A/76/222, A/77/171, A/78/246, A/79/263. including the development by the Special Rapporteur of the Model Protocol for Law Enforcement Officials to Promote and Protect Human Rights in the Context of Peaceful Protests and its supplementary components;
